EQE is related to the absorption of each photon in the SC and the number of electrons and holes that can be supplied to the external circuit. It is determined by the ratio of the flux of electrons from the SC to the flux of incident photons. EQE can be calculated from the distribution of the electric field intensity in the SC and the optical properties of the materials by the following Eq. (3):32EQEλ=∫2πcε0nλkλλEz,λ2dz.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
